headline: 3 Reasons to Sell TSN and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since June 2025, Tyson Foods has been in a holding pattern, posting a small return of 2.2% while floating around $57.04. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 14.1% gain during that period.
